---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Field · Porchlight">
  <h1>Field</h1>
  <p>
    A labeled form control — label, native input, and hint. Wraps real
    <code>&lt;input&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;select&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;textarea&gt;</code>
    so it inherits all native behavior (constraint validation, autofill, IME).
    State is driven by native pseudos and reflected onto the border/hint via
    <code>:has()</code> — no class toggles, no JS.
  </p>

  <h2>Text input</h2>
  <div class="demo">
    <label class="c-field">
      <span class="c-field__label">Workspace name</span>
      <input class="c-field__control" required placeholder="Acme Ops" />
      <span class="c-field__hint">Use a name your team recognizes.</span>
    </label>
  </div>

  <h2>Focus state</h2>
  <p>Focus the field below — the border shifts to the focus color and a soft accent glow appears (a border swap alone is below the perceptual threshold).</p>
  <div class="demo">
    <label class="c-field">
      <span class="c-field__label">Email</span>
      <input class="c-field__control" type="email" placeholder="you@example.com" />
      <span class="c-field__hint">Focus me to see the glow.</span>
    </label>
  </div>

  <h2>Invalid state</h2>
  <p>Type something invalid then tab away — <code>:user-invalid</code> fires on blur, so an empty required field doesn't scream on load.</p>
  <div class="demo">
    <label class="c-field">
      <span class="c-field__label">Workspace URL</span>
      <input class="c-field__control" type="url" required placeholder="https://" />
      <span class="c-field__hint">Must be a valid https:// URL.</span>
    </label>
  </div>

  <h2>Disabled</h2>
  <div class="demo">
    <label class="c-field">
      <span class="c-field__label">Read-only key</span>
      <input class="c-field__control" value="pk_live_••••" disabled />
      <span class="c-field__hint">Copied automatically on focus.</span>
    </label>
  </div>

  <h2>Checkboxes &amp; radios</h2>
  <p>
    Native checkbox/radio/range/color inputs inherit the brand accent
    automatically (set in the base layer) — no custom widgets, no JS. Pair them
    with a <code>.choice-group</code> for accessible, aligned lists.
  </p>
  <div class="demo choice-grid">
    <fieldset class="choice-group">
      <legend class="choice-group__legend">Notifications</legend>
      <label class="choice">
        <input type="checkbox" checked />
        <span>Send receipts</span>
      </label>
      <label class="choice">
        <input type="checkbox" checked />
        <span>Weekly summary</span>
      </label>
      <label class="choice">
        <input type="checkbox" />
        <span>Product updates</span>
      </label>
    </fieldset>
    <fieldset class="choice-group">
      <legend class="choice-group__legend">Billing plan</legend>
      <label class="choice">
        <input type="radio" name="plan" checked />
        <span>Monthly</span>
      </label>
      <label class="choice">
        <input type="radio" name="plan" />
        <span>Annual — save 20%</span>
      </label>
    </fieldset>
  </div>

  <h2>Density</h2>
  <div class="demo" data-density="compact">
    <label class="c-field">
      <span class="c-field__label">compact</span>
      <input class="c-field__control" placeholder="compact density" />
    </label>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .demo {
    padding: var(--pl-space-5);
    margin-block-end: var(--pl-space-4);
    background: var(--pl-color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--pl-color-border);
    border-radius: var(--pl-radius-lg);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--pl-space-3);
  }

  /* Choice groups (checkbox/radio lists) — a common SaaS settings pattern.
     Native inputs carry accent-color from the base layer; this just aligns. */
  .choice-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 16rem), 1fr));
    gap: var(--pl-space-5);
  }
  .choice-group {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    border: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--pl-space-2);
  }
  .choice-group__legend {
    padding: 0;
    margin-block-end: var(--pl-space-1);
    font-size: var(--pl-text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--pl-color-text-muted);
  }
  .choice {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--pl-space-2);
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .choice input {
    inline-size: 1.0625rem;
    block-size: 1.0625rem;
    margin: 0;
    /* accent-color comes from the base layer (:root). */
  }
  .choice:hover span {
    color: var(--pl-color-accent);
  }
</style>
